Description: Local Linux backup tool with seekable pax+zstd archives
 TimeTraveller is a local backup tool focused on trustworthy backups and
 fast, partial recovery.
 .
 Each backup is a pax archive compressed with zstd, alongside a small
 sidecar index that enables single-file restore in seconds — no need to
 scan the whole archive. Plans run on a cron schedule or manually; the
 GUI lets you browse archive contents and restore individual files,
 directories, or arbitrary selections.
 .
 Features include incremental backups with cycle-aware retention, glob
 patterns for excludes, explicit handling of nested mount points, and
 NAS destinations over NFS. Two plan types are supported: Active
 (scheduled, with retention) and Archive (manual, keep-forever for
 rarely-changing data).
